==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gluconic
<hw>Glu*con"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to, or
derived from, glucose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Gluconic acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>an
organic acid, obtained as a colorless, sirupy liquid, by the oxidation
of glucose; -- called also <altname>maltonic acid</altname>, and
<altname>dextronic acid</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glucose</ent>⟦br⟧
